Description: Fragment of neck and shoulder of Klazomenian black-figured pottery amphora; large ridge at base of neck; inside reserved; exterior: part of palmette and tendril; traces of added red on heart of volute and alternate leaves and added white dots around volute and on alternate leaves; ridge glazed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GH.142)
